{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840463020,"sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","part":{"id":"prt_d7857046b001xVcDNXauoniLwU","messageID":"msg_d7856e4be001hHSEl3GvglxLVE","sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0fef4c0f5e8747b493542a2b0be1ff30","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n22:   - `shared_types.go` with `AuthModeType` enum and `TargetPort` type\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** reading the file\n33: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n34: - AND `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`\n35: - AND `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL be `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type definition\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter struct shape\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n45: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreter` struct definition\n46: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec CodeInterpreterSpec` and `Status CodeInterpreterStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList struct shape\n49: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n50: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterList` struct definition\n51: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []CodeInterpreter` with JSON tag `items`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: CRD markers on CodeInterpreter\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n55: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n56: - **THEN** the `CodeInterpreter` type SHALL have:\n57:   - `+genclient` marker\n58:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n59:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n60:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n61:   - `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced` marker\n62:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` marker\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec definition\n67: \n68: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with fields for sandbox template, session management, warm pool, and authentication.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n72: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct\n73: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n74:   - `Ports []TargetPort` with JSON tag `ports` (optional)\n75:   - `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with JSON tag `template` (required)\n76:   - `SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout` (optional, default 15m)\n77:   - `MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration` (optional, default 8h)\n78:   - `WarmPoolSize *int32` with JSON tag `warmPoolSize` (optional)\n79:   - `AuthMode AuthModeType` with JSON tag `authMode` (optional, default picod)\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Template field is required\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n83: - **WHEN** examining the `Template` field markers\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` marker\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n87: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n88: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n93: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: AuthMode enum and default\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** examining the `AuthMode` field marker\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n100:   - `+kubebuilder:default=picod` marker\n101:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none` marker\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate definition\n106: \n107: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` for configuring code interpreter pods.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate fields\n110: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n111: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` struct\n112: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n113:   - `Labels map[string]string` with JSON tag `labels` (optional)\n114:   - `Annotations map[string]string` with JSON tag `annotations` (optional)\n115:   - `RuntimeClassName *string` with JSON tag `runtimeClassName` (optional)\n116:   - `Image string` with JSON tag `image` (optional)\n117:   - `ImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy` with JSON tag `imagePullPolicy` (optional)\n118:   - `ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference` with JSON tag `imagePullSecrets` (optional)\n119:   - `Environment []corev1.EnvVar` with JSON tag `environment` (optional)\n120:   - `Command []string` with JSON tag `command` (optional)\n121:   - `Args []string` with JSON tag `args` (optional)\n122:   - `Resources corev1.ResourceRequirements` with JSON tag `resources` (optional)\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets list markers\n125: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n126: - **WHEN** examining the `ImagePullSecrets` field\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n128:   - `+patchMergeKey=name` marker\n129:   - `+patchStrategy=merge` marker\n130:   - `+listType=map` marker\n131:   - `+listMapKey=name` marker\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus definition\n136: \n137: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with conditions and readiness flag.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n140: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n141: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct\n142: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n143:   - `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions` (optional)\n144:   - `Ready bool` with JSON tag `ready` (optional)\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n147: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n148: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n150:   - `+optional` marker\n151:   - `+listType=atomic` marker\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: AuthModeType enum definition\n156: \n157: The system SHALL define `AuthModeType` in `shared_types.go` as an enum for authentication modes.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AuthModeType type definition\n160: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n161: - **WHEN** reading the file\n162: - **THEN** `AuthModeType` SHALL be defined as `type AuthModeType string`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants\n165: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n166: - **WHEN** reading the file\n167: - **THEN** the following constants SHALL be defined:\n168:   - `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"`\n169:   - `AuthModeNone AuthModeType = \"none\"`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n174: \n175: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreter\n178: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n179: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n180: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreter) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreter)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterList\n183: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n184: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n185: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterList) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSpec\n188: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n189: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n190: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSpec)` SHALL exist and correctly copy pointer fields including `Template`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`, and `WarmPoolSize`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n193: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n194: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n195: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate)` SHALL exist\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterStatus\n198: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n199: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n200: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterStatus)` SHALL exist\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: DeepCopyObject implementation\n203: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n204: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n205: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n210: \n211: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers for CodeInterpreter.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n214: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n215: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n216: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n219: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n220: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n221: - **THEN** `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` SHALL include `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Generated informer for CodeInterpreter\n224: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n225: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n226: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Generated lister for CodeInterpreter\n229: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n230: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n231: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `CodeInterpreters(namespace string)` methods\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: REST resource plural\n234: - **GIVEN** the generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n235: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n236: - **THEN** the REST resource plural SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: JSON serialization\n241: \n242: The system SHALL ensure all types serialize correctly to/from JSON with camelCase field names.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON serialization\n245: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance with all fields populated\n246: - **WHEN** serializing to JSON\n247: - **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase field names: `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, `warmPoolSize`, `authMode`, `pathPrefix`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON deserialization\n250: - **GIVEN** a JSON document with camelCase field names\n251: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreter`\n252: - **THEN** all fields SHALL be correctly populated including nested `Template` and `Ports` slice\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Default values applied on deserialization\n255: - **GIVEN** a JSON document without `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, and `authMode` fields\n256: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreterSpec` with defaulting enabled\n257: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` SHALL default to `15m`\n258: - AND `MaxSessionDuration` SHALL default to `8h`\n259: - AND `AuthMode` SHALL default to `picod`\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: List type markers\n264: \n265: The system SHALL use correct Kubernetes list type markers for slice fields.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Ports list type\n268: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n269: - **WHEN** examining the `Ports` field in `CodeInterpreterSpec`\n270: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Conditions list type\n273: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n274: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field in `CodeInterpreterStatus`\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Environment list type\n278: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n279: - **WHEN** examining the `Environment` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Command list type\n283: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n284: - **WHEN** examining the `Command` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n285: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Args list type\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n289: - **WHEN** examining the `Args` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775840462985,"end":1775840463019}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840463022,"sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","part":{"id":"prt_d78570864001svtf7QB7Z7F05a","messageID":"msg_d7856e4be001hHSEl3GvglxLVE","sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f88f71c446fe4260aabfdc2e67d1f59b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n6: \n7: 1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n8: 2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n9: 3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n10: 4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n19: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n20: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n21: \n22: ### Type Definitions Required\n23: \n24: #### AgentRuntime\n25: \n26: ```\n27: AgentRuntime\n28: ├── Spec\n29: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: targetPort)\n30: │   ├── Template (*SandboxTemplate, JSON: podTemplate, required)\n31: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, JSON: sessionTimeout, default: 15m)\n32: │   └── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, JSON: maxSessionDuration, default: 8h)\n33: ├── Status\n34: │   └── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition, optional)\n35: └── List: AgentRuntimeList\n36: ```\n37: \n38: #### CodeInterpreter\n39: \n40: ```\n41: CodeInterpreter\n42: ├── Spec\n43: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n44: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n45: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n46: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n47: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n48: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n49: ├── Status\n50: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n51: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n52: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### Supporting Types\n56: \n57: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with optional pathPrefix/name, required port (uint32), protocol (HTTP|HTTPS)\n58: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n59: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n60: - `SandboxTemplate`: Labels, annotations, and embedded `corev1.PodSpec`\n61: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.\n62: \n63: ### Out of Scope\n64: \n65: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n66: - Webhook validation logic\n67: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n68: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n69: - HTTP API handlers (`pkg/api/`)\n70: \n71: ## Impact Analysis\n72: \n73: ### Upstream Dependencies\n74: \n75: | Dependency | Impact |\n76: |------------|--------|\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n78: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for embedded PodSpec in templates |\n79: \n80: ### Downstream Consumers\n81: \n82: | Consumer | Usage |\n83: |----------|-------|\n84: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n85: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers to `client-go/` |\n86: | Workload Manager (`cmd/workload-manager`) | Reads CRD specs to create Sandbox/SandboxClaim |\n87: | Router (`cmd/router`) | May reference CRD types for routing logic |\n88: | E2E Tests | Validates CRD creation and behavior |\n89: | Helm Chart | Ships generated CRD YAML for installation |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Version Stability**: Using `v1alpha1` signals API instability; changes may break existing workloads\n94: - **Field Defaults**: Kubebuilder markers set defaults at CRD level; changing defaults affects existing unlabeled resources\n95: - **Enum Values**: Adding/removing enum values (ProtocolType, AuthModeType) requires CRD schema update\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Use Unstructured CRDs\n100: \n101: **Approach**: Define CRDs via raw YAML without Go types, consume via `dynamic.Client`.\n102: \n103: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n104: |--------|------------|\n105: | Pros | No code generation dependency; faster initial setup |\n106: | Cons | No type safety; no informer/lister generation; harder validation; no IDE support |\n107: \n108: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires typed clients for controller-runtime integration and test reliability.\n109: \n110: ### Alternative 2: Single Unified CRD\n111: \n112: **Approach**: Merge AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter into one CRD with a `type` discriminator field.\n113: \n114: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n115: |--------|------------|\n116: | Pros | Fewer CRDs; simpler client-go generation |\n117: | Cons | Schema complexity; divergent status fields (`ready` only for CodeInterpreter); authMode only applies to CodeInterpreter; warmPoolSize only for CodeInterpreter |\n118: \n119: **Decision**: Rejected. The two CRDs serve distinct use cases with sufficiently different spec structures.\n120: \n121: ### Alternative 3: External Template Reference\n122: \n123: **Approach**: Use `TemplateRef` (name/namespace) instead of embedded template.\n124: \n125: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n126: |--------|------------|\n127: | Pros | Reusable templates; smaller CRD instances |\n128: | Cons | Additional lookup step; template lifecycle complexity; no inline customization |\n129: \n130: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. Inline templates match agent-sandbox conventions and simplify the user experience. May consider as future extension.\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 4: Duration as int64 seconds\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Use `int64` for timeout/duration fields instead of `metav1.Duration`.\n135: \n136: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n137: |--------|------------|\n138: | Pros | Simpler serialization; no string parsing |\n139: | Cons | Non-standard K8s API; human readability reduced (e.g., \"8h\" vs 28800) |\n140: \n141: **Decision**: Rejected. `metav1.Duration` follows Kubernetes API conventions and provides human-readable defaults (\"15m\", \"8h\").\n142: \n143: ## Risks\n144: \n145: | Risk | Mitigation |\n146: |------|------------|\n147: | Kubebuilder marker typos | Run `make gen-crd` and verify output YAML |\n148: | Missing JSON tags | Use `golangci-lint` with tag-related rules |\n149: | PodSpec embedding complexity | Follow `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` patterns |\n150: | Code-generator version mismatch | Pin `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 per `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header via `make gen-copyright`\n155: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions (e.g., `targetPort`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`)\n156: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply `+kubebuilder:object:root`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:default`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`\n157: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` for `Age` column\n158: \n159: ## References\n160: \n161: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n162: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n163: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n164: - Spec: `changes/AR-001/spec.md`\n165: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n\n1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840462986,"end":1775840463021}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840463024,"sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","part":{"id":"prt_d7856f4a7001rNpT3GXbLQ2VQG","messageID":"msg_d7856e4be001hHSEl3GvglxLVE","sessionID":"ses_287a93498ffeFhL5U8XVgdSX8y","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-46bbfd00f78a49bfb40bc9ed058841fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n6: \n7: 1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n8: 2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n9: 3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n10: 4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n19: | Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n20: \n21: ### Type Definitions Required\n22: \n23: #### CodeInterpreter\n24: \n25: ```\n26: CodeInterpreter\n27: ├── Spec\n28: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n29: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n30: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n31: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n32: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n33: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n34: ├── Status\n35: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n36: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n37: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n38: ```\n39: \n40: #### Supporting Types\n41: \n42: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, imagePullPolicy, imagePullSecrets\n43: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none authentication modes\n44: \n45: ### Out of Scope\n46: \n47: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n48: - Webhook validation logic\n49: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n50: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n51: - AgentRuntime CRD (handled in AR-001)\n52: \n53: ## Impact Analysis\n54: \n55: ### Upstream Dependencies\n56: \n57: | Dependency | Impact |\n58: |------------|--------|\n59: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n60: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for PodSpec elements (EnvVar, PullPolicy, ResourceRequirements) |\n61: \n62: ### Downstream Consumers\n63: \n64: | Consumer | Usage |\n65: |----------|-------|\n66: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n67: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers |\n68: | Workload Manager | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim instances from CodeInterpreter specs |\n69: | Router | Routes code interpreter requests to appropriate sandboxes |\n70: \n71: ## Alternatives Considered\n72: \n73: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n74: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n75: | **Inline Template (corev1.PodSpec)** | Direct reuse of Kubernetes types, familiar API | Too permissive, includes fields not relevant to code interpreters (init containers, volumes, etc.) | Rejected |\n76: | **Separate WarmPool CRD** | Decoupled warm pool lifecycle management | Adds complexity, warm pool is tightly coupled to interpreter spec | Rejected |\n77: | **AuthMode as string (no enum)** | Flexible for future modes | No validation, prone to typos | Rejected - use typed enum |\n78: | **Embed SandboxTemplate from AgentRuntime** | Code reuse, consistency | Different requirements (AgentRuntime uses full PodSpec, CodeInterpreter needs lighter template) | Rejected - use dedicated CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate |\n79: | **Status with multiple condition types** | Rich status reporting | Over-engineering for S-size task | Rejected - keep simple with Conditions + Ready |\n80: \n81: ## Risks\n82: \n83: | Risk | Mitigation |\n84: |------|------------|\n85: | Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n86: | AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n87: | Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |\n88: \n89: ## Implementation Notes\n90: \n91: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header\n92: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions\n93: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply validation markers for required fields and enums\n94: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add Age column for `kubectl get` output\n95: \n96: ## References\n97: \n98: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n99: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n\n1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n| Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840462976,"end":1775840463023}}}}
